title: Upstate New York lacrosse Hall of Fame inducts 7 new members on Sunday
text:
Upstate New York lacrosse Hall of Fame inducts 7 new members on Sunday ryan powell.JPG Syracuse's Ryan Powell aims for the goal during the game aganist Colgate at the Lacrosse Tournament they hosted this weekend at Coyne Field in Syracuse. Colgate #28 Nate Morse (upper right) and Colgate goal keeper #1 Paul Abrahimzadeh (right) try to block the shot. He scored on the shot. Photo by Lisa Krantz 1997 Comments 
Syracuse, N.Y. â€” The Upstate New York chapter of U.S. Lacrosse will induct seven local lacrosse legends and one great team at its annual Hall of Fame Induction Celebration dinner on Sunday at Traditions at the Links in East Syracuse. 
The inductees include Greg Burns, Sue Gallagher, Gordon Pollard, Ryan Powell, Barry Powless, Greg Rinaldi, John Zulberti and the Henninger High School 1980 lacrosse team. 
Since the Upstate NY Chapter of the lacrosse Hall of Fame started in 1990, 100 inductees have entered the Hall. 
Reservations for the dinner event may be made through chapter President Noel Ebner at (315) 317-0857. The celebration includes a 5 p.m. cocktail reception, 6 p.m. dinner followed by the inductions into the Hall. Tickets are $50.
